.</div><div id="R5" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-firstauthor"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-snm">Healy</span><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-fnm">JC</span></span>, Reznek RH. The peritoneum, mesenteries and omenta: normal anatomy and pathological processes. <em>Eur Radiol</em>1998; 8: 886–900.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s003300050485">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/9683690/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Eur+Radiol&amp;publication_year=1998&amp;pages=886&amp;doi=10.1007%2Fs003300050485&amp;pmid=9683690">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">6.</div><div id="R6" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-firstauthor"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-snm">Zhao</span><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-fnm">Z</span></span>, Liu S, Li Z, et al. Sectional anatomy of the peritoneal reflections of the upper abdomen in the coronal plane. <em>J Comput Assist Tomogr</em>2005; 29: 430–437.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1097/01.rct.0000164259.91057.af">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16012296/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=J+Comput+Assist+Tomogr&amp;publication_year=2005&amp;pages=430&amp;doi=10.1097%2F01.rct.0000164259.91057.af&amp;pmid=16012296">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">7.</div><div id="R7" class="citations"><div class